fr.sorbonne_u.cps.dht_mapreduce.interfaces.endpoints

Interface ContentNodeCompositeEndPointI<CAI extends ContentAccessCI,MRI extends ParallelMapReduceCI,DHTMI extends DHTManagementCI>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    fr.sorbonne_u.components.endpoints.AbstractEndPointI, fr.sorbonne_u.components.endpoints.BCMCompositeEndPointI, fr.sorbonne_u.components.endpoints.CompositeEndPointI, ContentNodeAsyncCompositeEndPointI<CAI,MRI>, ContentNodeBaseCompositeEndPointI<CAI,MRI>, java.io.Serializable

    public interface ContentNodeCompositeEndPointI<CAI extends ContentAccessCI,MRI extends ParallelMapReduceCI,DHTMI extends DHTManagementCI>
extends ContentNodeAsyncCompositeEndPointI<CAI,MRI>
    The interface ContentNodeCompositeEndPointI declares the signatures of the methods used in the definition of a software entity (object, component, SOA service, etc.) representing a content node in the DHT in an implementation-independent manner.

    Description

    A content node has three connection points, or end points: content access (adding, getting and removing data), DHT management (load management, etc.) and map/reduce (perform data-wise computations). The descriptor, used to facilitate the connections among clients of these end points and nodes providing them in the DHT, allows to retrieve descriptors (of type EndPointI) for each of them using the methods declared in this interface.

    Invariants

     invariant       true        // no more invariant

    Created on : 2024-06-24

    Author:
    Jacques Malenfant
